  "local_port": 40996,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I check my last 3 charges in Vodafone?",
  "response": "Checking your recent charges with Vodafone can be done through several convenient methods, including the Vodafone website, the My Vodafone app, SMS services, or by contacting customer support directly. Below are the detailed steps for each method:\n\n### 1. **Using the Vodafone Website**\n\n**Step-by-Step Guide:**\n\n1. **Visit the Official Website:**\n   - Go to your country-specific Vodafone website. For example, in the UK, visit [vodafone.co.uk](https://www.vodafone.co.uk/).\n\n2. **Log In to Your Account:**\n   - Click on the \"Log in\" button, usually located at the top right corner.\n   - Enter your Vodafone username/email and password. If you haven't registered yet, you may need to create an account using your Vodafone mobile number.\n\n3. **Navigate to the Billing Section:**\n   - Once logged in, look for sections labeled \"My Account,\" \"Billing,\" or \"Manage My Account.\"\n   - Click on the billing section to view your recent charges.\n\n4. **View Recent Charges:**\n   - You should see a detailed breakdown of your last few bills or transactions.\n   - Look for the specific charges you\u2019re interested in. Most interfaces will display the last 3-5 charges prominently.\n\n### 2. **Using the My Vodafone App**\n\n**Step-by-Step Guide:**\n\n1. **Download and Install the App:**\n   - If you haven't already, download the \"My Vodafone\" app from the [Apple App Store](https://apps.apple.com/app/my-vodafone/id518991937) or [Google Play Store](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.vodafone.myvoda).\n\n2. **Log In to Your Account:**\n   - Open the app and sign in using your Vodafone credentials. If you're a new user, register using your mobile number and follow the on-screen instructions.\n\n3. **Access the Billing Section:**\n   - Once logged in, tap on the menu icon (usually three horizontal lines) and select \"Billing\" or \"Account.\"\n\n4. **Review Your Charges:**\n   - The app will display your recent bills and charges. You can click on each bill to see detailed transactions, including the last three charges.\n\n### 3. **Via SMS or USSD Codes**\n\n*Note: The availability of SMS or USSD services can vary by country. Below is a general approach.*\n\n**Using USSD Codes:**\n\n1. **Dial the Billing USSD Code:**\n   - Open your phone\u2019s dialer and enter the specific USSD code provided by Vodafone for viewing bills. Common codes include `#1345#` or similar. Check your local Vodafone website for the correct code.\n\n2. **Follow the Prompts:**\n   - After dialing, follow the on-screen instructions to navigate to your billing information.\n\n3. **View Charges:**\n   - The system will display your recent charges, typically up to the last three transactions.\n\n**Using SMS Services:**\n\n1. **Send a Billing Request:**\n   - Compose an SMS with a specific keyword like \"BILL\" or \"CHARGE\" as per your local Vodafone guidelines.\n\n2. **Send to the Designated Number:**\n   - Send the SMS to the Vodafone billing number (e.g., 123).\n\n3. **Receive Your Charges:**\n   - You will receive an SMS detailing your recent charges and balance.\n\n*Ensure to check your Vodafone carrier\u2019s specific instructions as keywords and numbers may vary.*\n\n### 4. **Contacting Vodafone Customer Support**\n\n**Step-by-Step Guide:**\n\n1. **Find the Customer Support Number:**\n   - Visit the Vodafone website or check your Vodafone account documents for the correct customer support number in your region.\n\n2. **Call the Support Center:**\n   - Dial the customer support number and follow the voice prompts to reach the billing or account information section.\n\n3. **Verify Your Identity:**\n   - Be prepared to provide your account details or answer security questions to verify your identity.\n\n4. **Request Your Recent Charges:**\n   - Once connected to a representative or through the automated system, request the details of your last three charges.\n\n### **Additional Tips:**\n\n- **Ensure Secure Access:** Always access your Vodafone account through official channels to protect your personal information.\n- **Keep Credentials Handy:** Having your account number, PIN, or password available can expedite the process.\n- **Check for App Updates:** Make sure your My Vodafone app is updated to the latest version for the best user experience.\n- **Understand Your Plan:** Familiarize yourself with your Vodafone plan details to better understand the charges on your bill.\n\nIf you encounter any issues or discrepancies with your charges, contacting Vodafone customer support directly is the best course of action to resolve them promptly.",
